amdgpu: uvd_v4_2 — Round 2 Ghidra fixes (mc_resume / clkdiv / LMI_VM_VBASE)

After 18 v70..v76e iterations + 2-round Ghidra dig of orbis-12.02.elf
(findings doc:
 checkpoint/docs/research/uvd-bringup/2026-05-15-orbis-uvd-baikal-decoded.md)
this corrects three divergences from Sony's verbatim
uvd_vcpu_start_baikal that prior iterations introduced:

1. k = 4 (was 15) + new ps4_uvd_clkdiv module param.
   Sony source annotates ctx[+0x40] as "clock divider hint, low 4 bits".
   Session-4 SBL work measured FB_DIV=0x04 via mainline mmGCK_SMC_IND.
   Two independent signals -> k=4 is canonical. Module param lets us
   override empirically if hardware disagrees, no rebuild needed.

2. Remove inlined mc_resume body.
   3-way variant diff (Baikal/Liverpool-early/Gladius decompiles) confirmed
   none of Sony's three vcpu_start variants do mc_resume's UDEC_ADDR_CONFIG
   or LMI_ADDR_EXT/EXT40 setup. v76d-beta-2-A14's "re-enable mc_resume but
   skip UDEC" was a guess that contradicts Sony source. Removed.
   Also removes the v76b zero-LMI_ADDR_EXT writes (those were paired with
   mc_resume).

3. LMI_VM_VBASE = fw_gpu_addr (was 0).
   v76a regressed v73/v74/v75's correct fw_gpu_addr write to literal 0
   on the (incorrect) theory that Sony's ctx[+0x88] is uninitialized.
   Round 2 Ghidra confirmed: FUN_c88f9010 maps Region 1 to UVD-VMID VA
   0x300000000 and stores it in ctx[+0x88]. So Sony writes
   LMI_VM_VBASE = 0x300000000 (not 0). With our patches 0042-0044 mirroring
   firmware at GART VA 0x300000000, fw_gpu_addr equals 0x300000000 too.
   Either expression is correct; we use lower/upper_32_bits(fw_gpu_addr)
   for clarity that this is the firmware's GPU-side address.
   The "VM fault page 0x300000 vmid 4" symptom from v76a-onward was
   exactly because UVD was being told its firmware lives at addr 0.

Risk register: see Section F of the findings doc. Pre-conditions Linux
may not reproduce remain the open risk; diagnostic prints (already in
0034 + 0045 + 0049) will catch the failure if it persists.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <17146298+meerzulee@users.noreply.github.com>
